## QMeter Architecture Diagrams

### High-Level Component Diagram

```mermaid
graph TD
    A[UI/Config] --> B(Orchestrator);
    B --> C{Benchmark Modules};
    C --> D[Scoring];
    D --> E(Export);

    subgraph "Benchmark Modules"
        C1[Memory Test]
        C2[Algorithm Test]
        C3[Quill Speed Test]
        C4[Propagation Test]
        C5[Dataset-Store Test]
    end

    B -- Manages --> C;
    C -- Feeds results to --> D;
```

### Sequence Diagram: Interactive Mode

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant User
    participant QMeter_UI
    participant Orchestrator
    participant Benchmark_Modules

    User->>QMeter_UI: Clicks "Run Test"
    QMeter_UI->>Orchestrator: RunBenchmark()
    Orchestrator->>Benchmark_Modules: DelegateBenchmarkJob()
    Benchmark_Modules-->>Orchestrator: Benchmark results
    Orchestrator-->>QMeter_UI: Test complete
    User->>QMeter_UI: Clicks "Export..."
    QMeter_UI->>Orchestrator: ExportRun()
    Orchestrator-->>User: results.xml
```

### Sequence Diagram: Headless Mode

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant QServer
    participant Orchestrator
    participant Benchmark_Modules
    participant File_System

    QServer->>Orchestrator: Startup with /custom=runandexport
    Orchestrator->>Benchmark_Modules: RunBenchmark() & DelegateBenchmarkJob()
    Benchmark_Modules-->>Orchestrator: Benchmark results
    Orchestrator->>Orchestrator: Daemon_Heartbeat detects completion
    Orchestrator->>File_System: ExportRun() to C:\QMeter\results.xml
```

### Data-Flow Diagram: Score1/4/16 Computation

```mermaid
graph TD
    A[Raw Benchmark Results] --> B{Group by Category & Concurrent Datasets};
    B --> C{Calculate Average Runtime per Group};
    C --> D{Normalize against Gold Standard};
    D --> E[Final Scores: Score1, Score4, Score16];

    subgraph "Input"
        A
    end

    subgraph "Processing"
        B
        C
        D
    end

    subgraph "Output"
        E
    end
```
